When it comes to burgers, they are a good choice of snack or an accompaniment, especially with fries or potato wedges. A good burger should not fall apart and the bite should be soft and moist, for you not to choke. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Using a pan lightly butter each bun until crispy then set aside. Step 2 To create beef parties, Form each 2-ounce portion of beef into thin (bun sized) patties and generously season all sides with salt and pepper. Step 3 Pour 3 tablespoons of vegetable oil into the pan and place the beef parties for 3 minutes on each side. Step 4 Top each patty with a slice of American cheese and close the pan lid for 1 minute or until the cheese starts melting. Step 5 Remove the beef from the pan, fry the onion rings and bacon then set aside. Step 6 Stuck each bun with BBQ sauce, patties with cheese, bacon and onion rings. Add desired sauce or topping then top with the other bun slice. Serve and enjoy with a cold smoothie.